we prepare transformative educators to teach at the elementary, middle, and high school levels through our credential programs. these programs are post-baccalaureate, offered at the graduate level, and are accredited by the california commission on teacher credentialing (cctc). our primary academic opportunities include a multiple subject / elementary education or single subject / secondary education credential, a credential plus a master of arts in teaching (mat) degree or, for experienced teachers, a reading and literacy leadership specialist credential program with a master of arts in education (curriculum and instruction) degree. learn more about each of our academic opportunities by selecting the links below. phone: 408-924-3771 email: teacher-education@sjsu.edu social media: @sjsulurie 